  "texts": [
    "The recent study [91] has exposed vulnerabilities of GC and injected malicious information into condensed graphs to backdoor the GNNs trained on them.",
    "This highlights concerns over additional threats, such as adversarial attacks [60] and inference breaches [118], which pose significant challenges for deploying GC in security-sensitive domains, including confidential communications, financial systems, and industrial controls.",
    "In light of these challenges, the development of secure, privacy-preserving GC algorithms becomes imperative.",
    "E. Explainable Graph CondensationAnother promising avenue for GC research is the development of explainable GC methods.",
    "A relevant work [56] utilizes explainable algorithms to assess the importance of condensed nodes and prune the condensation redundancy."
  ],
